<plot>After the storied filming of "Apocalypse Now" wrapped in the Philippines in 1977, an unlikely team of film and sound editors, designers, technicians and artists under the direction of maverick Francis Coppola toiled for nearly two years to created the remarkable soundtrack for Apocalypse Now, using the then brand new six-channel stereo surround format. This is the untold story of their remarkable journey captured by documentary film cameras.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?233116</url></doc>
